post_text: Dear Twin Cedars students, lets talk school work. Yes our building is closed and we are unable to be in the classroom together but please remember teachers are providing lots of opportunities for you to continue your education. Please utilize these things such as Google Classroom, Grade specific Zooms, or you and a teacher Zooming together for help, packet activities that teachers have delivered, even domestic opportunities such as learning about cooking, cleaning, organizing etc.. Even if you only do an hour a day that is better than nothing!! It is not ok for you to not do anything. We have around 12 days left. We are here to help. Remember you can email us at our school emails. Twin Cedars website, Information tab, Faculty email address. We are all on there and we would love to hear from you!! Keep the learning going!!Finish strong!!

shared_text:
Twin Cedars School Nurse
April 12 at 5:48 PM Â·

Hey all! I know we are living in a crazy time right now and I wanted to make it easier for everyone to contact me (if needed) and for me to provide information and resources to everyone!

Since I'm new to TC I just thought I would introduce myself! I'm Joni Hannon the TC school nurse. I joined the TC family in December! I have been a nurse for 12 years and prior to coming to TC I was a surgery nurse at PRHC for 10 years and before that I was a Med/Surg nurse there. I'm a mom of 3, my oldest Easton is 9 and I have twins Liam and Kella who are 4. My husband Brad is an engineer for Musco. Outside of work I love to run and be outside with my family!

I hope you are all doing well. I am certainly missing all of our students and staff and can't wait til we can get back to school. If you having any questions or need anything please feel free to reach out to me!

Nurse Joni

I love that parents are getting to spend time with their kids and I myself am getting some projects around the house completed but if I could I would be in the classroom learning from them. As I said I like being at home to get some work done, but I love my classroom and students! Even in the summertime you can find me in the classroom, just ask the people out there cleaning ðŸ˜Š. I can put my house projects aside because school is like a â€œsecond skinâ€ for me. Today we learned that we will not be going back until April 30. Please know for the 70 students that I see everyday-I miss you. Parents if you need anything-let me know how I can help.

Reading through some of last year's "In a Million Words". I love doing these because it gives me an idea about the student and I love reading how the parents see their child.
"He likes video games and homemade chicken pot pie-oh and ice cream", "he loves sports-he enjoys playing them in the yard/ball field or on his X-Box and Playstation. His favorite teams are the Chicago Cubs and the Chicago Bears.", "she is very smart and energetic, at times she can be a handful. She likes to help when she can and loves to spend camping and outdoor stuff.", "he is one of the most special people I have ever met. He has a very kind and good heart. He looks forward to learning an instrument. He loves going to TC, he has taught me far more than I have taught him.", "Loves all sports and spending time with his family and friends. He enjoys recess and math." These are from 4th and 5th graders. I am excited to read the new ones as parents write again and see how the students have grown and changed! Getting excited for school!!
